✅ 1) Introduction to HTTP

HTTP = HyperText Transfer Protocol
It is the communication rule between:
Client (Browser / App) and
Server (Backend / API)

📌 Example:
When you open google.com, your browser sends an HTTP request and Google sends an HTTP response.

👉 HTTP is stateless (server doesn’t remember you automatically, each requests are independent of each other).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 2) HTTP Methods (Most Important ⭐)

HTTP methods define what action you want to perform.

🔥 Common Methods:

Method		Meaning			Used for

GET		Read data		Fetch user details

POST		Send data		Register / Login

PUT		Update full data	Replace user profile

PATCH		Update partial data	Update only phone number

DELETE		Remove data		Delete user

📌 Interview line:

GET is used to retrieve data, POST is used to send data to server for creation.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 3) HTTP Lifecycle (Request → Response Flow ⭐⭐)

This is how HTTP works step-by-step:

* User enters URL / clicks button
* Browser sends HTTP Request
* Server processes it (logic + DB)
* Server sends HTTP Response
* Browser shows output

Example:
Client → Request → Server
Client ← Response ← Server

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 4) HTTP Status Codes (Most Important ⭐⭐)

Status codes tell what happened with the request.
🔥 Main categories:

Code Range	Meaning

1xx	Informational

2xx	Success

3xx	Redirection

4xx	Client error

5xx	Server error

⭐ Most asked status codes:

Code	Meaning

200	OK (success)
201	Created (POST success)
204	No Content
301	Permanent redirect
302	Temporary redirect
400	Bad Request
401	Unauthorized (no login)
403	Forbidden (no permission)
404	Not Found
500	Internal Server Error
502	Bad Gateway

📌 Interview line:

401 is authentication issue, 403 is authorization issue.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 5) HTTP Headers (Very Important ⭐)

Headers are extra information sent with request/response.
Examples:
✅ Request headers:
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer token
Accept: application/json

✅ Response headers:
Set-Cookie
Cache-Control
Content-Type

📌 Interview line:
Headers carry metadata like authentication tokens, content type and caching rules.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 6) HTTP Cookies (Very Important ⭐)

Cookies are small data stored in browser sent to server with requests.

Used for:
✅ login sessions
✅ remember user
✅ tracking

Example:

Server sends cookie using Set-Cookie
Browser stores it
Next request automatically includes cookie

📌 Interview line:
Cookies help maintain session because HTTP is stateless.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 7) Overview of HTML

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to create the structure of web pages.
HTML is not a programming language, it is markup language.

👉 HTML tells the browser:
	what is a heading
	what is text
	where is image, form, button, etc.

🔹 Example
<h1>Hello World</h1>
<p>This is my first webpage</p>

🧠 Browser understands:
	h1 → heading
	p → paragraph

