✅ 10) Tags vs Elements vs Attributes ⭐⭐

🔹 Tag
A tag is a keyword enclosed in angle brackets (< >) that tells the browser what type of content it is.

<p>     <!-- opening tag -->
</p>    <!-- closing tag -->
<img>   <!-- self-closing tag -->

🔹 Element
An element = opening tag + content + closing tag
<p>Hello</p>

🔹 Attribute
Attributes provide extra information about elements.
It is always written inside the opening tag.
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter name">
•	type → attribute
•	"text" → value
Common Attributes : id, class, src, href, style, title

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 11) Inline vs Block Elements (Interview Favorite ⭐⭐)

🔹 Block Elements
	Take full width
	Start on new line
	Can contain inline and block elements

<div>Box 1</div>
<div>Box 2</div>

➡️ These will appear one below the other

✔ Examples:
div, p, h1–h6, form, section

🔹 Inline Elements
	Take only required width
	Stay in same line
	Cannot contain block elements

<span>Hello</span>
<span>World</span>

➡️ These appear on the same line

✔ Examples:
span, a, img, input, strong

