✅ 13) Web Storage ⭐⭐

HTML5 introduced Web Storage API to store data inside the browser.
👉 It stores data as key–value pairs

🔹 What is localStorage?
	Stores data permanently in browser
	Data remains even after browser restart

localStorage.setItem("username", "Raj");
let user = localStorage.getItem("username");
console.log(user); // Raj

🔹 Use Cases
	Theme (dark/light)
	Remember username
	User preferences

🔹 What is sessionStorage?
	Stores data temporarily
	Data removed when tab/browser closes

sessionStorage.setItem("otp", "1234");
sessionStorage.getItem("otp");

🔹 Use Cases
	OTP
	Temporary form data

