❓ Q2. What are semantic tags? Give examples

Answer:
Semantic tags clearly describe the meaning of content.
Semantic HTML tags are tags that clearly describe their meaning and purpose to both:
•  the browser
•  the developer
•  search engines (SEO)
•  screen readers (accessibility)

❌ Non-semantic example

<div id="header">
<div id="nav">
<div id="content">
<div id="footer">

Here, a browser does not understand what these sections represent.

✅ Semantic example

<header>
<nav>
<main>
<footer>
Now the browser understands the structure and role of each section.

Common Semantic Tags

Tag		Meaning
<header>	Top section of page
<nav>		Navigation links
<main>		Main content
<section>	Logical section
<article>	Independent content
<aside>		Sidebar content
<footer>	Bottom section



Why important?

1\. Better Readability
Code becomes self-explanatory.

2\. SEO (Search Engine Optimization)
Search engines can rank content better when structure is clear.

3\. Accessibility
Screen readers understand page structure → helps visually impaired users.

4\. Easy Maintenance
Developers can quickly understand and modify code.

